Peru Stocks: Austral, Buenaventura, Cerro Verde, Maple, Pomalca

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-26T21:16:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/peru-stocks-austral-buenaventura-cerro-verde-pomalca-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose 1 percent to 22,307.17. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 0.7 percent to 2,799.08.  Industrial and mining stocks rose as companies in the
general index reported better-than-forecast second-quarter
earnings and metals advanced in New York and  London , said
Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., rose 4.7 percent to $45.30.
Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner, climbed 1.6 percent to $42.65. The
company is scheduled to report second-quarter earnings after
markets close today.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian
gold and copper exploration company, gained 3.7 percent to 56
cents.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 3.4 percent to $1.23 and
Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll Seafood ASA,
gained 3 percent to 34 centimos.  Sugar producers rose after prices climbed for the fourth
day in five in New York.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, jumped 6.2 percent to 17.10 soles after
BBVA Banco Continental analyst German Estrada began coverage of
the stock with a ”market outperform” rating. Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo,
gained 4 percent to 52 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  